Captain Syrezeaju 16-Apr-20 04:57 PM
There was the familiar sound of the transporter initiating and then the following swirl of light; golden particles swirling and suspended in the middle and a figure forming amongst them. This figure wore medical whites and an ensign rank insignia; having been handed them and a certificate of graduation, given a congratulations, and then dragged off and told to change so he would blend in when he beamed aboard. The rank felt surreal. On one hand it meant that he had done it, he had graduated, but on the other it merely reminded him of the circumstances. There was no ceremony, no party with friends. Instead there was just him, an attempt to look different and older and wiser than before, and the anxiousness that things were still going to go wrong. With a slow inhale to brace himself he headed out into the hallway - head down, and praying there wouldn't be anyone to encounter along the way. (edited)
